## Preparation:
1. **Navigate to ATT&CK Navigator**:
    - Go to [MITRE ATT&CK Navigator](https://mitre-attack.github.io/attack-navigator) and click the select icon.
2. **Select a Threat Group**:
    - In the menu that pops up, select a threat group from the drop-down menu.
3. **Assign Technique Scores**:
    - In the technique controls, click the score icon and assign a value of 3 to all techniques.
4. **Set Color Preset**:
    - In the layer controls, click on "Color Setup" and assign a preset color scheme.
5. **Export Heat Map**:
    - In the layer controls, click "Export" and then the camera icon to create an SVG file of the heat map.
6. **Print the Heat Map**:
    - Print out the SVG file. You are now ready to play!

## Rules:
1. **Choose an APT Group**:
    - Each player selects an APT (Advanced Persistent Threat) group and prints out their navigator heat map.
2. **Balancing the Game**:
    - Some APT groups have more Techniques, Tactics, and Procedures (TTPs) than others. If a player chooses a group with fewer TTPs, they may have an advantage. Choose wisely!
3. **Host Calls Techniques**:
    - The host runs the MITRE ATT&CK Threat Bingo program, calling out a technique on each spin.
4. **Cross Off Techniques**:
    - Players cross off the techniques on their heat map as they are called out.
5. **Winning the Game**:
    - The first player to cross off all techniques on their APT group's heat map is the winner!

Enjoy playing MITRE ATT&CK Threat Bingo and may the best threat group strategist win!